#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int num = 5;
    long fact = 1;

    for (int i = 1; i <= num; i++) {
        fact *= i;
    }

    printf("Factorial: %ld\n", fact);

    return 0;
}
```

This program defines a variable `num` with the value 5, and initializes a variable `fact` to 1. The for loop iterates from 1 to `num`, multiplying each number by `fact`. Finally, it prints out the result of `fact`.

